article.headline: Tennessee Tech 42, Samford 21
article.story:
COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Anthony Ash rushed for 105 yards and
three TDs and freshman Cameron Kirnes added 102 yards and one TD as
Tennessee Tech beat Samford 42-21 Saturday.

Ash had TD runs of 2 yards and 10 yards in the first half and 14
yards in the fourth quarter. Kirnes scored on a 1-yard run in the
third.

Tennessee Tech (3-6, 2-5 Ohio Valley Conference) fell behind 7-0
early in the game but built a 28-14 lead by halftime.

Samford (5-5, 4-3 OVC) pulled to 35-21 in the second half on a
1-yard run by Adrian Bradley in the third quarter, but Ash's TD run
in the fourth locked up the win for the Golden Eagles.

Tech's Stephe Britton passed for 119 yards and one TD.

Samford's J. Adcock threw for 220 yards and 2 TDs.
